<main id="main">
    <h1>Tags</h1><div id="preamble">
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Tags are keywords that can be used to mark data records in plentymarkets. Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » Tags</strong> to create and manage tags. These tags can be linked to data records in the following areas of plentymarkets:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Board</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Category</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Ticket</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Contact</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Variation</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Order</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="50">1. Assigning rights for back end users</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Users of the type <strong>Back end</strong> can only access limited areas and menus in plentymarkets. Thus, their access to the system is limited. If you want users of this type to work with tags, an <strong>Admin</strong> user has to assign them rights as listed in the following.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Assigning rights for back end users:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Settings » User » Rights » User</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Use the search function (<span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-search" style="color:blue"></i></span>) and open the user account that should be edited.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the <strong>Authorisations</strong> area, activate the rights as listed in <a href="#table-tags-required-rights-back-end-user">Table 1</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> (<span class="icon"><i class="fa fa-save" style="color:green"></i></span>) the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<table id="table-tags-required-rights-back-end-user" class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch">
